After I actually contemplated ending my miserable life. Spent the next week celibate, and now I’m careful to scan content out of fear.

So to those who think this is fucked, please know it gets way worse and to be happy with the fact you look at this with revulsion and not glad the messed up ending was not that bad.

For those who are curious about the series please I beg of you crush your curiosity with the power of a black hole. It’s not worth all the crap you go through nor the change in perspective it gives you.

Ignorance is bliss.

Honestly, I felt like emergence made me a lot more uncomfortable. The entire time, I wanted Saki to be able to break the drug addiction and actually have a good ending. What really killed me was the dream-sequence at the end showing her happy what-if life she could've had if her child had actually stayed alive. With this Saki, though, I think my brain disconnected from my emotions in the final chapter when her mom betrayed her and her chauffeur screwed her. Being "shown" a happy ending hits a lot harder than just having entirely bad endings, in my honest opinion. But, everyone feels different about different things. It can't be helped.
